Anyone have to fight the SA-X yet, she's pretty easy isn't she?  Then there's that Omega Metroid at the end which oyu can fight without taking any damage.  And she finally gets rid of that crappy suit and get the old suit back!  Yeah!<br>
*END SPOILERS*<br>
<br>
I ended it with 3:00:00 even.  I will feel so cheated if I had to get less than 3:00:00 to get the best ending...<br>
<br>
I got 56% of the items... sad...<br>
<br>
*spoilers?*<br>
The story at the end is good, cliche, but it's a very good plot twist that's slightly predictable but even if you do guess about it, you'll probably be a little off.<br>
*end spoilers?*<br>
<br>
Great story...<br>
<br>
<br>
So to sum it up in a 1 sentence review:<br>
<br>
Good game, crappy suit color scheme, great story, crappy bosses, good puzzle difficulty, stretched out power ups over too many different items(they killed the spazer dangit!!!), good new map system, funky enemies, and good maps, it's a good game, buy it now. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=prismrx>PrismRX</A> at: 12/3/02 3:35:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tamperedwith>TamperedWith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/5/02 9:06:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Metroid Fusion *spoilers*</span><hr size=1> Actually, you are able to fire diagonally-down: Hold down the L button, then press down on the D-pad. You'll also notice that while hanging from a ceiling, while holding down the L button, she'll be aiming in the same diagonal-down manner.<br>
<br>
Another note: at the end, she doesn't necessarily gain her suit back. If you look closely (during the narration cut-scene, showing her upper-body half in frontal view), it's the same 'fusion' suit, but with the old brown color scheme of her old suit.<br>
<br>
I admit, Metroid Fusion didn't have quite the same impact as what Super Metroid had. Then again, when I usually compare today's offerings to its predecessors, the old-timers can still strike an undisputable charm on you.<br>
